If you happen to be in Chongqing on June 5th, please do not be alarmed by the civil defense siren sounding between 10:30 AM and 10:42 AM. These atrocities resulted in over 30,000 immediate civilian deaths and more than 6,600 indirect casualties. To honor those lost in the bombings, Chongqing observes this annual memorial through the siren test.

text: A little sad that he didn't show actual "nightlife" as in exploring the actual life in the city during the evening/night and showing things like local spots, clubs and parties. I'm aware that this is hard when you're a popular streamer surrounded by hundreds of people but no one says Speed can't make "normal"/pre-recorded videos in China that don't reveal his real time location all the time and also have other advantages such as better and more immersive image quality (he could potentially film 8K/60FPS/HDR or even VR180/VR360 which would be truly next level and would feel like you're actually there), having a more intimate/meaningful setting, they could have better planning and post production/editing possibilities etc. (I'd just advice to not make too many cuts as that could feel too artificial/mainstream/Mr. Beast-style and I think a more calm/intimate unscripted/unedited experience could be better here, basically similar to his streams just pre-recorded). And if too many people recognize and follow him they could just drive to another location and film there. Of course that doesn't mean he should do this instead of live streaming as those have their own place. I'm just saying he could do some of these videos besides live streaming and they could be very successful, if you look at these "Walking through China in 4K/HDR" videos they have millions of views and if they'd featured Speed I bet they would have even more. At the end of the day it doesn't even matter that much if it's streamed or pre-recorded since the likelihood that you're able to meaningfully interact with Speed through the chat while he's streaming is basically zero anyways. So the main advantage of streaming really only is the feeling of knowing this is actually happening right now.
